<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-10-15T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-10-15T14:00:00-05:00" n="691" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d691">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 654.119/556</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SWG1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Sharp</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-10-15T15:00:00-04:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">October 15, 1918, 3 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>5909. For <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_MG1">McFadden</persName> [From War Trade Board]:</p>
                            <p>No. 375. Your 466, Embassy 4349, October 7, 11 p.m.<note n="1" xml:id="d691fn1">Not printed.</note> We are happy to note that
                                the Blockade appears to be satisfied with our views as to place of
                                holding Swiss negotiations as expressed in our <pb facs="0820" n="1654" xml:id="pg_1654"/> note to French High Commission,
                                    Washington.<note n="1" xml:id="d691fn2">See telegram No. 5771,
                                    Oct. 1, to the Ambassador in France, <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_1649">p. 1649</ref>.</note> It
                                would be entirely agreeable to us that after negotiations here have
                                been completed and agreement prepared, it be sent to Paris to be
                                contemporaneously ratified by the Associated Governments and the
                                Swiss Government.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LR1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>